  "details": "The Font Viewer application has been rewritten to match the new design used for GNOME 3 applications.It can now show an overview of all installed fonts and optimizes screen space usage when the application is maximized.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nIn text_to_glyphs in sushi-font-widget.c in gnome-font-viewer 3.34.0, there is a NULL pointer dereference while parsing a TTF font file that lacks a name section (due to a g_strconcat call that returns NULL).(CVE-2019-19308)",
